Package com.millicast

Class Subscriber

java.lang.Object
com.millicast.Client
com.millicast.Subscriber
public class Subscriber extends Client
The Subscriber class. Its purpose is to receive media by subscribing to a millicast stream. The stream must already exists and someone must publish media.

    • disconnect

      public boolean disconnect()
      Disconnect from Millicast. The websocket connection to Millicast will no longer be active after disconnect is complete. If the client is currently subscribing, the SDK will first stop the subscribing before disconnecting.
      Specified by:
      disconnect in class Client
      Returns:
      false if unable to reach a disconnected state, true otherwise.

    • subscribe

      public boolean subscribe()
      Subscribe to a Millicast stream. You must be connected first in order to subscribe to a stream. After trying，a successful subscribe results in the Listener's method onSubscribed being called.
      Returns:
      true if now trying to, or is already subscribing, false otherwise.

    • unsubscribe

      public boolean unsubscribe()

      Returns:
      false if unable to reach a disconnected state, true otherwise.

    • project

      public boolean project(String sourceId, ArrayList<Subscriber.ProjectionData> projectionData)
      Specify the source you want to receive. With the project method you can select and switch sources from the Millicast server and then forward the selected media to the subscriber, for each audio and video track.
      Parameters:
      sourceId - The source id you want to receive
      projectionData - The configuration of the track you want to receive.
      Returns:
      true if success false otherwise.
